Write $x^4 + 6x^2 + 25$ in the form $(x^2 + mx + n)(x^2 + ox + p)$, where $m, o, n, p$ are integers. Then, we have

\begin{align*}
x^4 + 6x^2 + 25 &= (x^2 + mx + n)(x^2 + ox + p) \\
&= x^4 + (m+o)x^3 + (n+p+mo)x^2 + (mp+on)x + np.
\end{align*}

Comparing coefficients, we have that $m+o = 0, n+p+mo = 6, mp+on = 0, np = 25$.

